uss the subject Serapiss origins give story similar that Plutarch Writing about 400 years after the fact Plutarch claimed that Ptolemy established the cult after dreaming colossal statue Sinope Anatolia His councillors identified statue the Greek god Pluto and said that the Egyptian name for Pluto was Serapis This name may have been Hellenization OsirisApis OsirisApis was patron deity the Memphite Necropolis and the father the Apis bull who was worshipped there and texts from Ptolemaic times treat Serapis the Greek translation OsirisApis But little the early evidence for Serapiss cult comes from Memphis and much comes from the Mediterranean world with reference Egyptian origin for Serapis Mark Smith expresses doubt that Serapis originated Greek form OsirisApiss name and leaves open the possibility that Serapis originated outside Egypt The cult Isis and Osiris continued Philae until least the 450s long after the imperial decrees the late 4th century that ordered the closing temples pagan gods Philae was the last major ancient Egyptian temple closed 